# Part 6: Visualization & Interpretation

## 6.1 Figure 1 — Three Diagnostic Panels

```python
plt.figure(figsize=(15,5))

plt.subplot(1,3,1)
plt.plot(train_losses)           # 5 points (1 per epoch)
plt.title("Train Loss")

plt.subplot(1,3,2)
plt.plot(grad_norms)             # ~1955 points (1 per step)
plt.title("Gradient Norm")

plt.subplot(1,3,3)
plt.plot(overall_sr_history)     # ~39 points (every 50 steps)
plt.title("Overall Stable Rank")
```

**What healthy plots look like:**

```
Train Loss          Gradient Norm         Overall Stable Rank
  │\                 │                     │
  │ \                │╱╲╱╲                 │         ╱────────
  │  \               │    ╲╱╲╱╲           │       ╱
  │   \──            │         ╲───        │─────╱
  │     \──          │                     │
  │       \─         │                     │
  └──────── Epoch    └──────── Step        └──────── Step

  ↓ Decreasing       Moderate & stable     Moderate & stable
  = Model learning   = Stable training     = Healthy attention
```

## 6.2 Figure 2 — Per-Layer Stable Rank

```python
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
for i in range(n_layer):
    plt.plot(per_layer_sr_history[i], label=f"Layer {i}")
plt.title("Stable Rank per Layer")
plt.legend()
```

**Expected patterns:**

```
Stable Rank
  │
  │  Layer 0 ─────────────────── (highest: early layers = broad, exploratory attention)
  │  Layer 1 ──────────────── 
  │  Layer 2 ─────────────
  │  Layer 3 ──────────
  │  Layer 4 ────────
  │  Layer 5 ──────              (lowest: deep layers = focused, task-specific attention)
  │
  └──────────────────────── Steps
```

This pattern (higher SR in early layers, lower in deep layers) is expected and healthy:

| Layer Depth | Expected Behavior | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Early (0-1) | High stable rank | Learning local features (edges, textures) — needs broad attention |
| Middle (2-3) | Moderate stable rank | Combining local features — selective but diverse |
| Deep (4-5) | Lower stable rank | Task-specific decisions — focused on discriminative features |

