# Summary

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Image 32×32] --> B[64 Patches]
    B --> C[Linear Embed 128-dim]
    C --> D[+ CLS + PosEmbed]
    D --> E["6× Diff-Attn Blocks"]
    E --> F[CLS Token]
    F --> G[10-class Output]
    
    E --> H[Stable Rank Monitor]
    E --> I[Grad Norm Monitor]
    G --> J[Cross-Entropy Loss]
    
    style E fill:#ff6b6b,stroke:#333,color:#fff
    style H fill:#4ecdc4,stroke:#333,color:#fff
    style I fill:#4ecdc4,stroke:#333,color:#fff
```

| What | How | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Image → Tokens | Conv2d patch embedding | Efficient, GPU-friendly |
| Token interaction | Differential Attention | Noise cancellation via dual-map subtraction |
| Per-token processing | FFN (expand → ReLU → compress) | Non-linear feature transformation |
| Gradient stability | Pre-LayerNorm + Residuals | Prevents vanishing/exploding gradients |
| Classification | CLS token → Linear | Dedicated aggregation token |
| Optimizer | AdamW | Adaptive LR + weight decay |
| Health monitoring | Grad norm + Stable rank | Detect attention collapse early |
